title:
Data and Analysis Results for the MoTrPAC PASS1B Rat White Adipose Tissue 
    Companion Paper
text: Contains data code necessary reproduce analyses appear “Sexual dimorphism multi-omic response exercise training rat subcutaneous white adipose tissue” (https://doi.org/10.1101/2023.02.03.527012). Differential analysis transcriptomics, proteomics, phosphoproteomics, metabolomics subcutaneous white adipose tissue -omics datasets. Enrichment analyses (FGSEA KSEA) -ome. Weighted Gene Co-expression Network Analysis -omes excluding proteomics. -representation analysis (ORA) performed WGCNA modules/clusters. data-raw/ folder contains code reproduce analyses. R script names match objects create, though scripts create multiple objects (WATSC_DA.R), given general names. Code reproduce figures likely added vignettes later date.

text: object class data.frame 146 rows 21 columns. plate integer; 96-well plate identifier (1--4). runseq integer; run order (1--146). platepos integer; position 96-well plate. pid integer; randomly generated 8-digit identifier used linkage phenotypic data. samples animal PID. bid integer; unique 5 digit identifier samples collected acute test/sample collection period. samples collected period BID. labelid integer; unique 11 digit specimen label identifier, originating collection site, provides link specimen processing used shipments biorepository. viallabel instances aliquots processed biorepository. omics_subset logical; whether sample selected -omics analysis. sex factor; sex rat levels "Female" "Male". timepoint factor; exercise training group. Either "SED" (sedentary) number weeks training ("1W", "2W", "4W", "8W"). total_ketones numeric; total ketone bodies (\(\mu\)mol/L). nefa numeric; non-esterified fatty acids (NEFA) (mmol/L). lactate numeric; lactate (mmol/L). glucose numeric; glucose (mg/dL). glycerol numeric; glycerol (mg/dL). glucagon numeric; glucagon (pmol). insulin numeric; insulin (pg/mL). insulin_iu numeric; insulin (\(\mu\)IU/mL) using conversion 1 pg/mL = 0.023 \(\mu\)IU/mL provided package insert. leptin numeric; leptin (pg/mL). corticosterone numeric; corticosterone (ng/mL). ins_gcg_ratio numeric; molar insulin/glucagon ratio. Calculated (insulin (pg/mL) / 5.804 (Da)) / glucagon (pmol). homa_ir numeric; Homeostatic Model Assessment Insulin Resistance (HOMA-IR). Insulin (\(\mu\)IU/mL) x glucose (mg/dL) / 405.
